RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 6F All Weather Track CR: 74. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PARTY FOUL broke alertly, established the early advantage and showed good speed into the turn, drew clear nearing the quarter marker, extended the lead in upper stretch and kept to task in the final furlong. MYSTIC TBILISI rated off of the early pace, advanced three wide on the turn, responded to firm urging inside of the furlong marker, could not impact the winner in the late stages but finished well to get up for place. SYNNIN AND WINNIN stalked the solid early fractions, chased his stablemate while two wide on the turn, lost ground to PARTY FOUL in upper stretch, raced on the left lead in deep stretch and was outfinished for place, while clear of the rest for show. WHISPER AND WINK a bit slow into stride early on, chased the pace from a two wide path on the turn, improved position in the drive but was unable to threaten in the late stages. RANCHO RED forwardly placed in the early stages, chased the solid pace from the rail on the turn and gave way in the drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 1M All Weather Track CR: 89. Claiming Purse 17000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MR NAVIGATOR rated nicely off of the early pace, well positioned through the backstretch run, saved ground to the quarter marker, angled three wide nearing the top of the lane, full of run approaching the furlong pole, overtook the battling top pair in mid-stretch, drew clear in the final sixteenth and was geared down in the final strides. SUMO forwardly placed in the early going, attended to the moderate fractions through the backstretch run, pressed NIGHT PROOF to the quarter marker, battled with that rival to mid-stretch, was outrun in the late stages by MR NAVIGATOR and stayed on in the final strides to dead heat for place. NIGHT PROOF broke alertly and assumed command of the early pace, set prompted fractions along the backstretch run, battled with SUMO to the furlong grounds, could not keep pace with the winner in deep stretch and held for a share of place on the line. STAR SAILOR stalked the pace into the first turn, raced three wide into the backstretch run, was outrun nearing the half-mile marker, chased three wide to the quarter pole, ran evenly to mid-stretch and lacked a late kick in the drive. SPEED GRAZY crowded at the start and was off a bit slowly, settled off of the early pace, raced three wide into the first turn, asked for run four wide on the far turn, ran on the left lead inside of the furlong marker and did not produce a late rally. BROOKYS TAPIT unhurried in the early stages, saved ground into the backstretch run, trailed into the second turn and did not threaten in the late going.

ENTRY.COMMENT: off step slowly,3wide 1st turn,asked 4wide 1/4,left lead,no rally

ENTRY.COMMENT: close up,attended pace,battled to 1/8,weakened late,dead heat 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 92. Claiming Purse 17000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MCGEORGE allowed to settle in the early stages, saved ground along the turn, mounted a steady inside bid commencing in upper stretch, came within aim inside of the furlong marker, assumed command in deep stretch and held in a drive in the final strides. SINGLE ME OUT chased the fast early pace from the inside, gained ground nearing the quarter marker, angled three wide for the drive, ran evenly to mid-stretch, was outfinished by MCGEORGE in the late stages but rallied in the final strides to secure the place. HOLIDAY HUSTLE took back off of the fast early pace, raced two wide on the turn, swung widest for the drive, finished well in deep stretch and just missed for place while securing the show. FURY KAP broke alertly, showed good early speed while disputing the pace inside of DIAMOND RANGER, contested the quick fractions with that rival to the quarter marker, battled to mid-stretch, drifted out in deep stretch, impeded DIAMOND RANGER and weakened in the final stages. DIAMOND RANGER forwardly placed in the early going, contested the fast pace with FURY KAP to the turn, took a narrow lead from that rival approaching the quarter marker, battled outside of FURY KAP to the furlong grounds, took up while in tight when that rival drifted out in deep stretch and gave way. AFFECTIONTO AUTISM chased the fast early pace, advanced two wide on the turn, swung four wide for the drive and tired in the stretch run. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE INCIDENT IN DEEP STRETCH INVOLVING FURY KAP AND DIAMOND RANGER. IN A UNANIMOUS RULING, THE STEWARDS DETERMINED FURY KAP DRIFTED OUT NEARING THE SIXTEENTH-MARKER, IMPEDED DIAMOND RANGER AND COST DIAMOND RANGER THE OPPORTUNITY OF A BETTER PLACING. FURY KAP WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM FOURTH AND PLACED FIFTH. THE RIDER OF DIAMOND RANGER ALSO LODGED AND OBJECTION AGAINST THE RIDER OF FURY KAP.

ENTRY.NAME: Single Me Out
ENTRY.OWNER: Big Iron Racing LLC and Slam Dunk Racing

ENTRY.NAME: Holiday Hustle
ENTRY.OWNER: Landeros David and Landeros Jorge T

ENTRY.NAME: Diamond Ranger
ENTRY.COMMENT: disputed pace,battled to 1/8,took up 1/16,gave way late

ENTRY.NAME: McGeorge
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled,saved ground,steady inside rally,held driving late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 97. Claiming Purse 21000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUCK'S ROYAL FLUSH broke alertly and showed good early speed, set a pressured pace to the turn, shook free nearing the quarter marker, drew clear into upper stretch, felt late pressure and dug in in the final strides to prevail. REFI NOW allowed to settle in the early stages, saved ground along the turn, rallied in upper stretch, closed well inside of the furlong marker to pressure LUCK'S ROYAL FLUSH, could not get by the determined winner in the final strides and held for place in a head bob on the wire. ALEXANDER'S DREAM chased the fast early pace, raced two wide on the turn, swung four wide for the drive, gained ground nearing mid-stretch, rallied in the final sixteenth and just missed for place while well clear of the rest for show. OH GREAT (IRE) stalked the fast early pace, raced three wide while in pursuit on the turn, swung five wide for the drive, was outrun in upper stretch and gave way in the late stages. THISMUSTBETHEPLACE showed early speed and disputed the fast pace to the turn, pressed LUCK'S ROYAL FLUSH to the quarter marker, encountered traffic and steadied while dropping back in upper stretch and was not a late factor. HANDR'SDREAM chased the fast early pace, raced in tight approaching the turn, clipped heels with OH GREAT, fell and unseated the jockey and was vanned off. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE INCIDENT INVOLVING HANDR'SDREAM APPROACHING THE TURN AND IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION RULED THAT HANDR'SDREAM CAME INTO TIGHT QUARTERS, CLIPPED HEELS AND LOST THE RIDER ON HIS OWN ACCORD AND THAT THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH BASED ON THE INCIDENT.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 5 5F All Weather Track CR: 79. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 15 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $2,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DR WYSONG bobbled at the start and was off a step slowly, was unhurried heading to the turn, saved ground to the quarter marker, swung four wide for the drive, improved position nearing the furlong pole, closed with a rush in the final furlong, overtook BOUNDFORJAMAICA in deep stretch and was up in the final strides to prevail. BOUNDFORJAMAICA crowded GARDEES WORLD in the opening stages, chased the fast early pace, gained ground two wide on the turn, swung four wide for the stretch run, loomed nearing mid-stretch, assumed command nearing the sixteenth-marker, was all out to hold off DR WYSONG in deep stretch, was tagged for the win in the final strides and was second best in the end. DEVINE DANCING hard sent after the break and set the fast pace to the turn, raced off of the rail while carving out quick fractions to the quarter marker, held foes at bay while on a clear lead to mid-stretch, weakened inside of the furlong pole and held for show. TAKES A VILLAGE forwardly placed in the early stages, tracked the quick pace from a two wide path on the turn, swung three wide for the drive, chased DEVINE DANCING to mid-stretch and lacked a late response. KISS RIDE GOODBYE settled in the second flight in the early stages, saved ground through the turn, swung two wide for the drive, improved position in the final sixteenth but did not threaten in the end. GARDEES WORLD fractious in the gate, was a bit slow into early stride then was crowded by BOUNDFORJAMAICA in the first furlong, lagged through the turn, swung two wide for the drive and improved position in the final stages but was not a factor. DESERT SMOKE prominent in the early going, lost ground while along the inside on the turn, was outrun in upper stretch and gave way in the final stages. BADGER GAL not far back in the early going, lost position while two wide on the turn, swung three wide for the drive and tired in the stretch run.

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased pace,lost ground inside turn,outrun upper,gave way

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 77. Claiming Purse 13400. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: INDIANERA tracked the fast early pace, saved ground on the turn, angled out and was roused four wide at the top of the lane, closed fast inside of the eighth pole to overtake RICKENBACHER and kept to task in the final strides to prevail. THE CALABRESE KID allowed to settle early on, raced two wide on the turn, swung four wide for the drive, mounted a bold late rally inside of the furlong pole, could not reel in INDIANERA in the late going but finished well to be second best in the end. DRUMADOON tracked the fast early pace, raced three wide on the turn, swung five wide for the stretch run, re-rallied inside of the furlong pole, could not match strides with the top pair in the final sixteenth but stayed on in the final strides to secure the show. TIZ A THRILL lunged at the start and was off a step slowly, settled in the second flight while not far back early on, advanced two wide on the turn, continued that bid to upper stretch, was outkicked in the drive and just missed for show in the final strides. SASQUATCH RIDE shuffled at the start and was off slowly, allowed to settle in the early going, raced three wide on the turn, swung six wide for the drive and closed willingly in the final stages. AWESOME CURLIN unhurried in the early going, raced two wide on the turn, trailed to the furlong marker, was not able to impact the leaders in deep stretch but improved position while gaining late. HOLYJAZZ tracked the fast early pace, saved ground while in pursuit of the loose leader on the turn, chased RICKENBACHER to mid-stretch and tired. RICKENBACHER broke alertly, showed good early speed and set fast fractions to the turn, sped to a long lead nearing the quarter marker, was in hand to mid-stretch, shied from the crop inside of the furlong pole, stopped nearing the sixteenth-marker and was overtaken in the final stages. TOM'S MOON allowed to settle, saved ground through the turn and did not threaten in the drive.

ENTRY.OWNER: RD Race Stable Inc Lavine Brian D Lavine David E and Lovett John

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 7 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 109. Allowance Purse 33000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since October 15 Allowed 3 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 5 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $50,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FREEPORT JOE settled off of the early pace while well positioned, saved ground into the backstretch run, remained in range to the half-mile marker, lost a bit of ground while waiting for racing room nearing the quarter marker, tipped out three wide nearing the eighth pole, chased I'MGONNABESOMEBODY to the sixteenth-marker, surged in deep stretch and determinedly prevailed. I'MGONNABESOMEBODY forwardly placed on the run into the first turn, prompted the moderate pace while outside of CRAZY DREAMS to the half-mile marker, confronted that rival nearing the quarter pole, drew to even terms in upper stretch and dueled to the furlong grounds, shook free and met the bid of FREEPORT JOE nearing the sixteenth-marker, was gamely bested in the final strides and was second best. CRAZY DREAMS assumed command in the early going and was sent to the early lead, set moderate fractions while prompted by I'MGONNABESOMEBODY to the half-mile marker, confronted by that rival nearing the quarter pole, dueled to mid-stretch, weakened in the final furlong and just saved third in the final strides. LAMMAS (GB) allowed to settle in the early going while in a good position, raced two wide into the backstretch run, advanced three wide nearing the quarter pole, outrun in upper stretch and lacked a late rally. RIMPROTECTOR unhurried in the early stages, not far back to the half-mile marker, steered two wide to the top of the lane and finished evenly in the drive.

ENTRY.OWNER: Charles, Ronald L. and Gordon, Samuel

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 1M All Weather Track CR: 99. Allowance Purse 31000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since October 15 Allowed 3 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 5 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won The Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AMERICA GREAT tracked the runaway leader from well behind while racing clearly in the second position, launched a bid from the three-eighths pole under a hard ride, gradually cut into the lead through the run to the wire, drifted out mid-stretch under left-handed urging, appeared to hang late when Orozco lost his crop, then found another gear when HOUSE OF LORDS was making a run to his outside and surged ahead yards from the finish line. HOUSE OF LORDS was content to settle at the head of the trailing pack behind TRIBAL NATION and AMERICA GREAT, bided time well into the far turn, launched a serious bid from the quarter pole, made a bold run on the outside, shied when AMERICA GREAT drifted into his path, continued to run on to gain the place. TRIBAL NATION hustled from the gate and sprinted clear of the field into the first turn, had a six length lead turning into the backstretch, widened into the far turn, hit the top of the stretch with a seemingly insurmountable lead then began to shorten strides in the final furlong yet managed to hold on for third. CHIEF WILD EAGLE got away a step slow then was pinched back and forced to steady near the seven-eighths pole, thereafter stuck behind a wall of horses into the first turn while eager to go on, settled down but was last through the first turn, angled over to the two path down the backstretch, relaxed nicely but remained at the rear of the field to the far turn, awaited racing room through the far turn, tipped out a path into the stretch but was still behind horses, found some room passing the eighth pole and finished with a rush. KODIACTION was away well, held good position near the front of the trailing group, moved out to the four path for the stretch run and finished well but came up a bit short. BIG FLAME last away but saved ground throughout, steadied near the five-sixteenths pole then rallied under urging, closing stoutly to be part of the blanket finish at the wire. GALLANT WARREN broke well and saved ground through the clubhouse turn, launched a rally from the seven-sixteenths pole while still on the inside, sustained that rally to deep stretch and finished with good energy. BUENISIMO off a bit slow, three wide and near the rear of the field into the first turn, seemed content with the position for the backstretch run, attempted to rally three furlongs to run but was unable to quicken and was not persevered with late. SUPERMAZEL broke out after the break, got hung out four wide into the first turn, remained wide down the backstretch, was getting out and drifted even wider on the far turn then was allowed to gallop out to the wire while hopelessly beaten. DEL MO raced three wide into the first turn, then was reserved early, traveling with the trailing pack well behind the early leader, was asked to pick up the pace on the far turn but had no response and was outrun from that point.
